==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bowssen
<hw>Bows"sen</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To drench; to
soak; especially, to immerse (in water believed to have curative
properties).</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There were many <qex>bowssening</qex> places, for curing of mad
men.⟦br⟧
. . . If there appeared small amendment he was <qex>bowssened</qex>
again and again.</q> <rj><qau>Carew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bowstring</ent>⟦br⟧
